<a name="program">
  <h2>Location</h2>
  The symposium will take place in Antwerpen, Belgium,
  at the University of Antwerp,
  campus Middelheim, building G "Wiskunde-Informatica".
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Belgium</strong> is easily reached by air, through the
    international <a
      href="http://www.brusselsairport.be">Brussels Airport</a>
    (not to be confused with "Brussels South" airport, which is
    actually in <a
      href="http://www.charleroi-airport.com">Charleroi</a>).
    <li><strong>Antwerpen</strong> is easily reached by car or by
    train, with two major train stations:
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Antwerpen-Central</strong> in city center of Antwerp.
      <li><strong>Antwerpen-Berchem</strong> is closer to the
      campus Middelheim of the university.
    </ul>
    From Brussels airport, every 15 minutes, you can take a train to Brussels
    North station. From there, you can take a train to
    Antwerp (both Central and Berchem; the train stops first in Berchem).
    The train connection from Brussels North to Antwerpen is very
    fast and frequent.
    <em>You can buy a ticket straight until
      Antwerp already at the airport.</em>
    <li><strong>Antwerp University, campus Middelheim,</strong>
    street address: Middelheimlaan 1, 2020 Antwerpen,
    is easily reached:
    <ul>
      <li><strong>from the city center by bus</strong>, line 32,
      you can take this bus in the Quellinstraat, this is the second street
      left off the
      De Keyserlei which is the main boulevard coming out of the
      central station.
      At peak hours there is a bus every 10 minutes.  Get off at the stop
      "Koninklijkelaan", this is right in front of the campus.
      You can ask the bus driver to warn you when to get off (ask
      for campus Middelheim of the university).  The trip takes
      20 to 23 minutes.
      <li><strong>from the city center by tram</strong>, line 15
      direction "Mortsel":
      this is a good alternative if you don't mind walking 500 meters.
In the city center you can take this tram (it runs frequently) in any of the
underground metro stations.  After just 12 minutes ride,
      get off at the stop "Koninklijkelaan" (by then
      the tram is no longer underground).  Although it has the
      same name, this is not the same
      stop as the bus stop mentioned above!  Now walk along the
      Koninklijkelaan ("Royal Lane") to the campus.
      <li> <strong>from station Antwerpen-Berchem</strong>, by
      bus line 32 (the same one as above, indeed it passes
      through Berchem).
    </ul>
  </ul>
